The vulnerable section of the code is:

```c++
for (curchar = parsestart; *curchar; curchar++) {
    //...
    param_buffer[param_len++] = *curchar;
    //...
}
```

To fix this vulnerability, you should add a check to ensure that the number of characters being copied into `param_buffer` does not exceed its size. You can do this by checking the value of `param_len` against `sizeof(param_buffer)` before copying the character. If the limit is reached, you should stop copying characters and handle the error accordingly.
